    <div id="places">

   
    <h3>Things To See In Deosai<h3>

    <h4>Bara Pani</h4>
    	
    <p>As the name suggests (big water), this is a river nearly in the middle of Deosai. There are two bridges that go over it. One is a bridge made of concrete foundations and wood throughout, whilst the other is made of rope mostly and a few pieces of wooden planks here and there. Many tourists go on the rope bridge, though this is very dangerous since there are large gaps and you can easily lose your footing. This is a great spot for taking photos with families and friends.</p>

    <img src="http://www.worldfortravel.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/Bara-Pani-Deosai.jpg" alt="Dangerous bridge crossing over Bara Pani" width="351" height="210"/>
    	
    <img src="http://mw2.google.com/mw-panoramio/photos/medium/16627884.jpg" alt="Bridge crossing over Bara Pani" width="351" height="210"/>

    <img src="https://c1.staticflickr.com/4/3013/2737303633_30dc55c9d4_b.jpg" alt="Jeep crossing a bridge" width="351" height="210"/>
    	
    <img src="https://c1.staticflickr.com/2/1510/24268040930_9c0a1da84e_b.jpg" alt="Dangerous bridge crossing over Bara Pani" width="351" height="210"/>

    <h4>Sheosar Lake</h4>
            
    <p>Sheosar Lake is a remarkable sight to behold. It looks like a flat bowl high among the mountains on a plains. The water is still and looks very serene. Often, this area is very windy and this fact is enjoyed by many of the people who visit here. From here you can catch a glimpse of the famous killer mountain; Nanga Parbat, and this view looks particularly cool in the winter, as shown in the picture at the top of the page.</p>

    <img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/e/e5/Blue_Lake%2C_Deosai%2C_Gilgit_Baltistan.jpg" alt="Sheosar Lake" width="351" height="210"/>
            
    <img src="http://hikers.pk/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/Sheosar-Lake-768x419.jpg" alt="Sheosar Lake" width="351" height="210"/>
            
    <img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/17/Sheoshar_Lake%2C_Deosai.jpg/1280px-Sheoshar_Lake%2C_Deosai.jpg" alt="Sheosar Lake" width="351" height="210"/>
            
    <img src="http://pakiholic.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/6-Sheosar-Lake-Deosai-National-Park-Gilgit-Baltistan-Pakistan-Uzair-Ahmed.jpg" alt="Sheosar Lake" width="351" height="210"/>

    <h4>Glacial Mountains</h4>

    <p>If you love adventure, then you will love the eipc backdrop Deosai provides; the snow-capped mountains, glaciers and fresh spring water. The wildlife, flowers, climate, grassland and serenity of the plateau combined with the surrounding mountains, glittering glaciers and crytal clear watercourses make this place a feel and look like heaven on Earth.</p>

    <img src="https://i.pinimg.com/474x/10/a2/25/10a225caf0829155db7c2b587ab7db47--the-heavens-heaven-on-earth.jpg" alt="Glaical mountains" width="351" height="210"/>

